Carapace (
Figs. 23–24
) small and rounded. LV overlapping RV. Carapace surface smooth and with shallow pits in dorsal-ventral area of carapace center. Males slightly larger than females or similar in size (
Figs. 23A–D
). Anterior and posterior margins of both valves without tubercles. Dorsal margin slightly ovoid, sloping posteriorly. Greatest height near center. Pore openings simple, with seta. Carapace ovoid, with greatest width near midlength in dorsal view (
Fig. 23E
). Ventral margin straight (
Fig. 23F
). Calcified inner lamella wider anteriorly than posteriorly in internal view (
Figs. 24A–D
). Inner list with anterior margin wider in RV than LV, with diamond-shaped ornamentations in wide area. Four central muscle scars present slightly below center (
Fig. 24E
). Color opaque to light brown.

Female description
: Carapace similar to male. A2 four-segmented, with short seta-like G2 claw about 1/3 of G1 and G3 claws (
Fig. 27C
). T1 with three unequally long and smooth apical setae with lengths: h2>h1≈h2 (
Fig. 27D
). Genital organ simple, rounded (not drawn). All other soft body parts similar to male.
